[{"question":"Was this guy a sleeper put into al Qaeda in the Yemen by the CIA or was it another twist?","answer":"Well, that\u0027s not clear at this point, or we just don\u0027t know those details yet.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":45,"aSentId":46},{"question":"What do you make of two things, I guess, one, the more sophisticated bomb that they were working on, but secondly, this whole notion, potentially of having sleepers, agents inside al Qaeda now?","answer":"ASTINGS: Well, first I think you look at it, Yemen has become the hot new battleground in the war on terror.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":52,"aSentId":53},{"question":"Why wouldn\u0027t they reveal all the details?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s clearly a big intelligence success for the Americans, for the Saudis.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"What would you imagine is going on now within al Qaeda as an overall organization?","answer":"They must have been in a state of panic.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":87,"aSentId":88},{"question":"Mr. Perkins, tell me why are you so implacably opposed to two loving people getting married?","answer":"Well, Piers, it\u0027s not just me, but North Carolina, as it looks like 60 percent of the voters there are poised to adopt the state amendment.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":113,"aSentId":114},{"question":"You treat it as a celebrity bag extension?","answer":"You know, Piers, I think that\u0027s a really question and I think a lot of people will ask that question of themselves, because quite frankly, marriage from -- among heterosexuals has not been good, when we see a divorce rate around 50 percent.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":123,"aSentId":124},{"question":"How much more damage can a gay couple do if they\u0027re married to the damage they can do to civilization if they\u0027re unmarried?","answer":"Yes, again, Piers, you\u0027re asking great questions because I think those are the questions that are going through people\u0027s minds.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":132,"aSentId":133},{"question":"You have five kids, right?","answer":"Yes, I do.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":163,"aSentId":164},{"question":"What would you do if one of them came home and said, dad, I\u0027m gay?","answer":"Well, we would have a conversation about it.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":165,"aSentId":166},{"question":"Are you ready for round two, Jonah?","answer":"I\u0027m struggling to contain my excitement.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":196,"aSentId":197},{"question":"I might come out a rabid fascist after the break, who knows?","answer":"Who knows.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":199,"aSentId":200},{"question":"I promise you were coming to this in detail but on the premise of liberal cliches, is it not a right-wing cliche to assume that anyone that disagrees with you on any kind o matter automatically has to be a screaming liberal?","answer":"I\u0027m glad you brought this up, because the one question you asked me on the last show about my book, I gave you the answer, and I said look, liberals and conservatives are like our ideological but conservatives admit it.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":223,"aSentId":224},{"question":"Then you must be -- you must be the least bulliable person ever created, aren\u0027t you?","answer":"I said you tried to bully me, I didn\u0027t say you bullied me.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":270,"aSentId":271},{"question":"If I was a liberal responding to the allegation that essential to your block, I\u0027d say, come on, Jonah, where is your ideology about gay marriage?","answer":"Look, I think we have a misunderstanding about ideology.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":314,"aSentId":315},{"question":"Is this another cheap bit of liberal cliche riddled nonsense?","answer":"It was FDR --","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":336,"aSentId":337},{"question":"What really compelled you to write this book?","answer":"Well, one of my great frustrations when I speak on college campuses, in particular, is how so many kids are taught to be deeply skeptical of ideological statements, but they\u0027ll let these cliches just sort sail right through.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":353,"aSentId":354},{"question":"Well, what is wrong with those two -- what is wrong with those two statements?","answer":"In terms of better 10 guilty men go free, right, if you look at it as an ideological statement, I have no problem with it.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":359,"aSentId":360},{"question":"And doesn\u0027t that inevitably lend to a more cliche ridden game?","answer":"Sure, absolutely.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":403,"aSentId":404},{"question":"But to sum up, Republicans are as bad at this as Democrats, right?","answer":"They can often be just as bad about as Democrats.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":417,"aSentId":418},{"question":"But can I assume what you\u0027re about to tell me is out of character?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":445,"aSentId":446},{"question":"Are you just trying to win the record for the most plugs in one minute?","answer":"Well, I am here.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":455,"aSentId":456},{"question":"Did you mean what you said about -- why do you feel so exercised about this tax issue?","answer":"Because it started off with -- I believed in him.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":480,"aSentId":481},{"question":"Really?","answer":"No.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":499,"aSentId":500},{"question":"You don\u0027t think people that ran Wall Street are responsible for a lot of the economic meltdown this country had to suffer?","answer":"Maybe some of it, but not all of it.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":501,"aSentId":502},{"question":"Who is more responsible, the very, very smart people who know exactly what they are offering or the people who are perhaps not so smart, not so well versed in the property market, in loans, in finance generally, who get seduced into accepting these and then lose everything?","answer":"Well, that\u0027s wrong, yes.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":504,"aSentId":505},{"question":"But who is more responsible?","answer":"I don\u0027t know.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":516,"aSentId":517},{"question":"And what is wrong with taxing the super rich a little bit more then the super poor?","answer":"Nothing.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":523,"aSentId":524},{"question":"How many are disaffected with Obama, do you think?","answer":"A lot, a lot more than they\u0027re saying.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":569,"aSentId":570},{"question":"Why shouldn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yeah, but I didn\u0027t argue that point.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":589,"aSentId":590},{"question":"Would they?","answer":"Yes, but he\u0027s putting people on the defensive.","docId":"120508pmt","qSentId":598,"aSentId":599}]